T1	Intervention 234 649	This study was performed to evaluate by echo-Doppler technique the hemodynamic effects of subcutaneous sumatriptan administration. Forty-one migraine subjects (26 males, 15 females), mean age 36 +/- 2 years (range 36-39 years), and 20 healthy control subjects (14 males, six females), mean age 36 +/- 2 years (range 36-39 years) were randomized (double-blind) to receiving sumatriptan (group A) or placebo (group B)
